title: Curiosities of Olden Times
creator: Sabine Baring-Gould
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Curiosities of Olden Times, by Sabine Baring-Gould. This book is a collection of 17 gems of random knowledge, such as what women are made of and the philosopher's stone, written in Baring-Gould's own style. (Summary by Carolin) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; fun-facts
